# sha256-pinned raw artifacts must stay byte-exact through git (invariant 2: raw is
# sacred). Never eol-convert them in either direction — a CRLF-bearing capture would
# be silently normalized at commit, and LF-bearing evidence would be smudged to CRLF
# on Windows checkouts; both break pin re-verification.
docs/regimes/*/evidence/** -text
crates/adapters/*/fixtures/** -text

# JOURNAL is append-only single-line dated entries (memory contract), so git's
# built-in union driver merges concurrent lane appends without conflicts
# (goal 097 parallel lanes). Caveat: server-side PR merges may ignore this —
# lanes merge main into their branch LOCALLY first (factory-lane.md step 6).
agents/JOURNAL.md merge=union
